WEBVTT

00:00:11.800 --> 00:00:20.580
recordings are in the public domain. For more information or to volunteer, please visit

00:00:33.780 --> 00:00:44.670
James Version, Chapter 1. Paul, called to be an apostle of Jesus Christ, through the

00:00:44.670 --> 00:00:54.630
of God. And Sophanes, our brother, unto the Church of God, which is at Corinth, to them that are

00:00:54.630 --> 00:01:03.170
sanctified in Christ Jesus, called to be saints, with all that in every place call upon the name

00:01:03.170 --> 00:01:13.970
of Jesus Christ our Lord, both theirs and ours. Grace be unto you, and peace from God our Father,

00:01:13.970 --> 00:01:23.450
and from the Lord Jesus Christ. I thank my God always on your behalf, for the grace of God,

00:01:23.850 --> 00:01:33.360
which is given you by Jesus Christ, that in every thing ye are enriched by him in all utterance and

00:01:33.510 --> 00:01:43.130
in all knowledge, even as the testimony of Christ was confirmed in you, so that ye come behind in

00:01:43.130 --> 00:01:52.370
no gift, waiting for the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ, who shall also confirm you unto the end,

00:01:52.650 --> 00:02:01.110
that ye may be blameless in the day of our Lord Jesus Christ. God is faithful, by whom ye were

00:02:01.110 --> 00:02:09.430
called unto the fellowship of his Son Jesus Christ our Lord. Now, I beseech you, brethren,

00:02:09.430 --> 00:02:17.470
by the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, that ye all speak the same thing, and that there be no

00:02:17.470 --> 00:02:26.110
divisions among you, but that ye be perfectly joined together in the same mind and in the same

00:02:26.110 --> 00:02:35.590
judgment. For it hath been declared unto me of you, my brethren, by them which are of the house of

00:02:36.030 --> 00:02:44.270
Christ, that ye may know that there are contentions among you. Now, this I say, that every one of you

00:02:44.270 --> 00:02:54.690
saith, I am of Paul, and I of Apollos, and I of Cephas, and I of Christ. Is Christ divided? Was Paul

00:02:54.690 --> 00:03:04.550
crucified for you, or were ye baptized in the name of Paul? I thank God that I baptized none of you,

00:03:04.550 --> 00:03:14.070
but Crispus and Gaius, lest any should say that I had baptized in my own name. And I baptized also

00:03:14.070 --> 00:03:22.870
the household of Stephanus. Besides, I know not whether I baptized any other. For Christ sent me

00:03:22.870 --> 00:03:30.230
not to baptize, but to preach the gospel, not with wisdom of words, lest the cross of Christ

00:03:30.230 --> 00:03:39.830
should be made of none effect. For the preaching of the cross is to them that perish foolishness.

00:03:40.450 --> 00:03:48.710
But unto us which are saved, it is the power of God. For it is written, I will destroy the wisdom

00:03:48.710 --> 00:03:55.950
of the wise, and will bring to nothing the understanding of the prudent. Where is the wise?

00:03:55.950 --> 00:04:03.850
Where is the scribe? Where is the disputer of this world? Hath not God made foolish the

00:04:03.850 --> 00:04:12.690
wisdom of this world? For after that in the wisdom of God the world by wisdom knew not God,

00:04:13.050 --> 00:04:21.550
it pleased God by the foolishness of preaching to save them that believe. For the Jews require a

00:04:21.550 --> 00:04:30.310
sign, and the Greeks seek after wisdom. But we preach Christ, crucified, unto the Jews a stumbling

00:04:30.310 --> 00:04:39.310
block, and unto the Greeks foolishness. But unto them which are called, both Jews and Greeks,

00:04:39.650 --> 00:04:47.970
Christ, the power of God and the wisdom of God. Because the foolishness of God is wiser than men,

00:04:47.970 --> 00:04:57.190
and the weakness of God is stronger than men. For ye see your calling, brethren, how that not many

00:04:57.190 --> 00:05:06.990
wise men after the flesh, not many mighty, not many noble, are called. But God hath chosen the

00:05:06.990 --> 00:05:14.090
foolish things of the world to confound the wise, and God hath chosen the weak things of the world

00:05:14.090 --> 00:05:22.150
to confound the things which are mighty, and base things of the world, and things which are despised

00:05:22.150 --> 00:05:31.650
hath God chosen, yea, and things which are not, to bring to naught things that are, that no flesh

00:05:31.650 --> 00:05:42.310
should glory in his presence, but of him are ye in Christ Jesus, who of God is made unto us wisdom

00:05:42.310 --> 00:05:49.690
and righteousness and sanctification and redemption, that according as it is written,

00:05:50.330 --> 00:05:59.250
he that glorieth, let him glory in the Lord. Chapter 2. And I, brethren, when I came to you,

00:05:59.590 --> 00:06:07.090
came not with excellency of speech or of wisdom, declaring unto you the testimony of God.

00:06:07.090 --> 00:06:17.170
For I determined not to know anything among you save Jesus Christ, and him crucified. And I was

00:06:17.170 --> 00:06:24.030
with you in weakness and in fear, and in much trembling, and my speech and my preaching was not

00:06:24.030 --> 00:06:31.610
with enticing words of man's wisdom, but in demonstration of the spirit and of power,

00:06:31.610 --> 00:06:39.370
that your faith should not stand in the wisdom of men, but in the power of God.

00:06:39.490 --> 00:06:47.050
Howbeit we speak wisdom among them that are perfect, yet not the wisdom of this world,

00:06:47.350 --> 00:06:54.690
nor of the princes of this world that come to naught. But we speak the wisdom of God in a

00:06:54.690 --> 00:07:02.110
history, even the hidden wisdom which God ordained before the world unto our glory,

00:07:02.510 --> 00:07:09.290
which none of the princes of this world knew. For had they known it, they would not have crucified

00:07:09.290 --> 00:07:20.070
the Lord of glory. But as it is written, I have not seen nor ear heard, neither have it entered

00:07:20.070 --> 00:07:27.590
into the heart of man the things which God hath prepared for them that love him.

00:07:28.390 --> 00:07:36.430
But God hath revealed them unto us by his Spirit. For the Spirit searcheth all things,

00:07:36.790 --> 00:07:46.490
yea, the deep things of God. For what man knoweth the things of a man save the

00:07:46.490 --> 00:07:57.670
spirit of man which is in him. Even so the things of God knoweth no man, but the Spirit of God.

00:07:58.610 --> 00:08:06.490
Now we have received not the spirit of the world, but the spirit which is of God, that we might know

00:08:06.490 --> 00:08:14.730
the things that are freely given to us of God. Which things also we speak, not in the words which

00:08:14.730 --> 00:08:23.570
man's wisdom teacheth, but which the Holy Ghost teacheth, comparing spiritual things with spiritual.

00:08:24.470 --> 00:08:31.250
But the natural man receiveth not the things of the Spirit of God, for they are foolishness unto

00:08:31.250 --> 00:08:40.810
him. Neither can he know them, because they are spiritually discerned. But he that is spiritual

00:08:40.810 --> 00:08:48.890
judgeeth all things, yet he himself is judged of no man. For who hath known the mind

00:08:48.890 --> 00:08:59.260
of the Lord, that he may instruct him? But we have the mind of Christ.

00:08:59.260 --> 00:09:03.780
Reading by Simon Wainwright

00:09:05.780 --> 00:09:11.020
CHAPTERS III AND IV of I Corinthians.

00:09:27.580 --> 00:09:31.420
Reading by Simon Wainwright.

00:09:32.620 --> 00:09:40.600
The First Epistle of Paul to the Corinthians, King James Version, Chapter 3.

00:09:41.220 --> 00:09:51.220
And I, brethren, could not speak unto you as unto spiritual, but as unto carnal, even as unto babes in Christ.

00:09:51.800 --> 00:10:06.080
I have fed you with milk and not with meat, for heather too ye were not able to bear it, neither yet now are ye able, for ye are yet carnal.

00:10:06.560 --> 00:10:15.820
For whereas there is among you envying and strife and divisions, are ye not carnal and walk as men?

00:10:15.820 --> 00:10:24.520
For while one sayeth, I am of Paul, and another, I am of Apollos, are ye not carnal?

00:10:25.140 --> 00:10:31.660
Who then is Paul, and who is Apollos, but ministers by whom ye believed?

00:10:32.400 --> 00:10:41.680
Even as the Lord gave to every man, I have planted, Apollos watered, but God gave the increase.

00:10:42.180 --> 00:10:50.320
So then, neither is he that planteth anything, neither he that watereth, but God that giveth the increase.

00:10:50.860 --> 00:11:04.920
Now, he that planteth and he that watereth are one, and every man shall receive his own reward according to his own labor, for we are laborers together with God.

00:11:04.920 --> 00:11:09.800
Ye are God's husbandry, ye are God's building.

00:11:10.500 --> 00:11:21.400
According to the grace of God which is given unto me as a wise master builder, I have laid the foundation, and another buildeth thereon.

00:11:21.760 --> 00:11:34.900
But let every man take heed how he buildeth thereupon, for other foundation can no man lay than that is laid which is Jesus Christ.

00:11:34.920 --> 00:11:50.100
Now, if any man build upon this foundation gold, silver, precious stones, wood, hay, stubble, every man's work shall be made manifest, for the day shall declare it,

00:11:50.700 --> 00:12:00.120
because it shall be revealed by fire, and the fire shall try every man's work of what sort it is.

00:12:00.120 --> 00:12:07.320
If any man's work abide which he hath built thereupon, he shall receive a reward.

00:12:07.920 --> 00:12:18.380
If any man's work shall be burned, he shall suffer loss, but he himself shall be saved, yet so as by fire.

00:12:19.100 --> 00:12:26.060
Know ye not that ye are the temple of God, and that the Spirit of God dwelleth in you?

00:12:26.680 --> 00:12:34.820
If any man defile the temple of God, him shall God destroy, for the temple of God is holy.

00:12:35.280 --> 00:12:39.440
Which temple ye are? Let no man deceive himself.

00:12:39.440 --> 00:12:50.020
If any man among you seemeth to be wise in this world, let him become a fool, that he may be wise.

00:12:50.780 --> 00:13:00.820
For the wisdom of this world is foolishness with God, for it is written, he taketh the wise in their own craftiness.

00:13:01.240 --> 00:13:08.900
And again the Lord knoweth the thoughts of the wise, that they are vain. Therefore let no man

00:13:08.900 --> 00:13:18.400
glory in men, for all things are yours, whether Paul, or Apollos, or Cephas, or the world, or life,

00:13:18.560 --> 00:13:28.860
or death, or things present, or things to come. All are yours, and ye are Christ's, and Christ is God.

00:13:31.180 --> 00:13:40.200
Let a man sow account of us, as of the ministers of Christ, and stewards of the mysteries of God.

00:13:40.580 --> 00:13:50.020
Moreover, it is required in stewards that a man be found faithful. But with me it is a very small thing,

00:13:50.480 --> 00:13:57.320
that I should be judged of you, or of man's judgment, yea, I judge not mine own self.

00:13:57.820 --> 00:14:09.320
For I know nothing by myself, yet am I not hereby justified, but he that judges me is the Lord.

00:14:09.880 --> 00:14:18.240
Therefore judge nothing before the time, until the Lord come, who both will bring to light

00:14:18.240 --> 00:14:23.580
the hidden things of darkness, and will make manifest

00:14:24.200 --> 00:14:30.720
the counsels of the hearts, and then shall every man have praise of God.

00:14:30.880 --> 00:14:38.740
And these things, brethren, I have in a figure, transferred to myself and to Apollos,

00:14:38.860 --> 00:14:46.300
for your sakes, that ye might learn in us not to think of men above that which is written,

00:14:46.880 --> 00:14:53.060
that no one of you be puffed up for one against another.

00:14:54.040 --> 00:15:01.340
For who maketh thee to differ from another, and what hast thou that thou dost not receive?

00:15:01.860 --> 00:15:10.760
Now, if thou dost receive it, why dost thou glory, as if thou hast not received it?

00:15:10.760 --> 00:15:20.820
Now ye are full, now ye are rich, ye have reigned as kings. Without us, and I would to God,

00:15:21.180 --> 00:15:30.460
ye did reign, that we also might reign with you. For I think that God have set forth us,

00:15:30.620 --> 00:15:39.320
the apostles, last as it were appointed to death. For we are made a spectacle unto the world,

00:15:39.320 --> 00:15:47.480
and to angels, and to men. We are fools for Christ's sake, but ye are wise in Christ.

00:15:47.840 --> 00:15:55.460
We are weak, but ye are strong. Ye are honorable, but we are despised.

00:15:56.000 --> 00:16:04.080
Even unto this present hour, we both hunger, and thirst, and are naked, and are buffeted,

00:16:04.080 --> 00:16:11.700
and have no certain dwelling place, and labor, working with our own hands.

00:16:12.320 --> 00:16:20.840
Being reviled, we bless. Being persecuted, we suffer it. Being defamed, we entreat.

00:16:21.580 --> 00:16:29.720
We are made as the filth of the world, and are the offscouring of all things unto this day.

00:16:29.720 --> 00:16:36.720
I write not these things to shame you, but as my beloved sons I warn you.

00:16:37.600 --> 00:16:45.020
For though ye have ten thousand instructors in Christ, yet have ye not many fathers.

00:16:45.520 --> 00:16:51.420
For in Christ Jesus, I have begotten you through the gospel.

00:16:52.260 --> 00:16:59.500
Wherefore I beseech you, be ye followers of me. For this cause have I sent unto you,

00:16:59.720 --> 00:17:07.180
Timotheus, who is my beloved son, and faithful in the Lord, who shall bring you

00:17:07.180 --> 00:17:16.240
into remembrance of my ways which be in Christ, as I teach everywhere in every church.

00:17:16.640 --> 00:17:23.860
Now some are puffed up as though I would not come to you, but I will come to you shortly,

00:17:23.860 --> 00:17:32.540
if the Lord will, and will know not the speech of them which are puffed up, but the power.

00:17:32.880 --> 00:17:41.410
For the kingdom of God is not in word, but in power. What will ye? Shall I come unto you with

00:17:41.410 --> 00:17:47.510
or in love, and in the spirit of meekness?

00:18:14.270 --> 00:18:18.290
V It is reported commonly that there was fornication

00:18:18.290 --> 00:18:25.210
and such fornication as is not so much as named among the Gentiles, that one should have his

00:18:25.210 --> 00:18:31.810
father's wife. And ye are puffed up, and have not rather mourned, that he that hath done this deed

00:18:31.810 --> 00:18:38.110
might be taken away from among you. For I verily, as absent in body, but present in spirit,

00:18:38.470 --> 00:18:43.670
have judged already as though I were present, concerning him that hath so done this deed.

00:18:44.190 --> 00:18:49.030
In the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, when ye are gathered together, and my spirit,

00:18:49.330 --> 00:18:55.890
with the power of our Lord Jesus Christ, to deliver such an one unto Satan for the destruction of the

00:18:55.890 --> 00:19:02.390
flesh, that the spirit may be saved in the day of the Lord Jesus. Your glorying is not good.

00:19:02.710 --> 00:19:08.310
Know ye not that a little leaven leaveneth the whole lump? Purge out therefore the old leaven,

00:19:08.310 --> 00:19:14.730
that ye may be a new lump, as ye are unleavened. For even Christ our Passover is sacrificed for

00:19:14.730 --> 00:19:20.630
us. Therefore let us keep the feast, not with old leaven, neither with the leaven of malice

00:19:20.630 --> 00:19:28.090
and wickedness, but with the unleavened bread of sincerity and truth. I wrote unto you in an epistle

00:19:28.090 --> 00:19:33.570
not to company with fornicators, yet not altogether with the fornicators of this world,

00:19:33.570 --> 00:19:40.650
or with the covetous, or extortioners, or with idolaters, for then must ye needs go out of the

00:19:40.650 --> 00:19:46.790
world. But now I have written unto you not to keep company, if any man that is called a brother,

00:19:47.170 --> 00:19:53.950
be a fornicator, or covetous, or an idolater, or a railler, or a drunkard, or an extortioner,

00:19:54.270 --> 00:20:00.230
with such an one know not to eat. For what have I to do, to judge them also that are without?

00:20:00.230 --> 00:20:06.470
Do not ye judge them that are within? But them that are without, God judgeth. Therefore put

00:20:06.470 --> 00:20:14.230
away from among yourselves that wicked person. Chapter 6. Dare any of you, having a matter

00:20:14.230 --> 00:20:20.770
against another, go to law before the unjust, and not before the saints? Do we not know that

00:20:20.770 --> 00:20:26.390
the saints shall judge the world? And if the world shall be judged by you, are ye unworthy

00:20:26.390 --> 00:20:33.250
to judge the smallest matters? Know we not that we shall judge angels? How much more things that

00:20:33.250 --> 00:20:39.730
pertain to this life? If then ye have judgments of things pertaining to this life, set them to judge

00:20:39.730 --> 00:20:46.670
who are least esteemed in the church. I speak to your shame. Is it so that there is not a wise man

00:20:46.670 --> 00:20:53.630
among you? No, not one that shall be able to judge between his brethren. But brother goeth to law

00:20:53.630 --> 00:21:00.230
with brother, and that before the unbelievers. Now therefore there is utterly a fault among you,

00:21:00.630 --> 00:21:07.670
because ye go to law one with another. Why do we not rather take wrong? Why do ye not rather suffer

00:21:07.670 --> 00:21:16.350
yourselves to be defrauded? Nay, ye do wrong and defraud, and that your brethren. Know we not that

00:21:16.350 --> 00:21:22.850
the unrighteous shall not inherit the kingdom of God? Be not deceived, neither fornicators,

00:21:22.850 --> 00:21:29.790
nor idolaters, nor adulterers, nor effeminate, nor abusers of themselves with mankind,

00:21:30.530 --> 00:21:37.510
nor thieves, nor covetous, nor drunkards, nor revilers, nor extortioners shall inherit the

00:21:37.510 --> 00:21:43.670
kingdom of God. And such were some of you, but ye are washed, but ye are sanctified,

00:21:43.990 --> 00:21:50.090
but ye are justified in the name of the Lord Jesus, and by the spirit of our God. All things

00:21:50.090 --> 00:21:55.970
are lawful unto me, but all things are not expedient. All things are lawful for me,

00:21:56.090 --> 00:22:02.710
but I will not be brought under the power of Aene. Meats for the belly, and the belly for meats,

00:22:03.270 --> 00:22:10.030
but God shall destroy both it and them. Now the body is not for fornication, but for the Lord,

00:22:10.390 --> 00:22:17.190
and the Lord for the body. And God hath both raised up the Lord, and will also raise up us

00:22:17.190 --> 00:22:23.970
by his own power. Know ye not that your bodies are the members of Christ? Shall I then take the

00:22:23.970 --> 00:22:31.230
members of Christ, and make them the members of Anharlot? God forbid. What? Know ye not that he

00:22:31.230 --> 00:22:38.870
which is joined to Anharlot is one body? For two, saith he, shall be one flesh. But he that is

00:22:38.870 --> 00:22:46.290
joined unto the Lord is one spirit. Flee fornication. Every sin that a man doeth is without the body,

00:22:46.290 --> 00:22:54.530
but he that cometh fornication sinneth against his own body. What? Know ye not that your body is the

00:22:54.530 --> 00:23:02.310
temple of the Holy Ghost which is in you, which ye have of God, and ye are not your own? For ye

00:23:02.310 --> 00:23:08.710
are bought with a price. Therefore glorify God in your body, and in your spirit, which are God's.

00:23:16.310 --> 00:23:19.110
March 2011

00:23:21.110 --> 00:23:25.290
CHAPTERS SEVEN AND EIGHT

00:23:25.290 --> 00:23:27.590
Of I Corinthians

00:23:49.350 --> 00:23:58.870
The first epistle of Paul to the Corinthians, King James Version, Chapter Seven.

00:24:01.330 --> 00:24:05.590
Now, concerning the things whereof ye wrote unto me,

00:24:06.090 --> 00:24:09.310
it is good for a man not to touch a woman.

00:24:09.630 --> 00:24:15.390
Nevertheless, to avoid fornication, let every man have his own wife,

00:24:15.390 --> 00:24:19.730
and let every woman have her own husband.

00:24:20.750 --> 00:24:26.090
Let the husband render unto the wife due benevolence,

00:24:26.390 --> 00:24:29.950
and likewise also the wife unto the husband.

00:24:30.790 --> 00:24:35.090
The wife hath not power of her own body, but the husband,

00:24:35.430 --> 00:24:41.770
and likewise also the husband hath not power of his own body, but the wife.

00:24:41.770 --> 00:24:49.010
Defraud ye not one the other, except it be with consent for a time

00:24:49.010 --> 00:24:53.610
that ye may give yourselves to fasting and prayer,

00:24:54.470 --> 00:25:02.530
and come together again that Satan tempt you not for your incontancy.

00:25:03.090 --> 00:25:07.390
But I speak this by permission and not of commandment,

00:25:08.170 --> 00:25:13.790
for I would that all men were even as I myself.

00:25:14.310 --> 00:25:21.390
But every man hath his proper gift of God, one after this manner and another after that.

00:25:22.030 --> 00:25:25.250
I say therefore to the unmarried and widows,

00:25:25.690 --> 00:25:30.910
it is good for them if they abide even as I,

00:25:31.270 --> 00:25:34.950
but if they cannot contain, let them marry.

00:25:34.950 --> 00:25:42.970
For it is better to marry than to burn, and unto the married I command.

00:25:43.890 --> 00:25:50.910
Yet not I, but the Lord, let not the wife depart from her husband.

00:25:51.770 --> 00:25:56.890
But, and if she depart, let her remain unmarried,

00:25:57.130 --> 00:26:03.070
or be reconciled to her husband, and let not the husband put away his wife.

00:26:03.070 --> 00:26:08.150
But to the rest speak I, not the Lord.

00:26:08.810 --> 00:26:12.330
If any brother hath a wife that believeth not,

00:26:12.690 --> 00:26:17.710
and she be pleased to dwell with him, let him not put her away.

00:26:18.230 --> 00:26:23.030
And the woman which hath a husband that believeth not,

00:26:23.570 --> 00:26:27.970
and if he be pleased to dwell with her, let her not leave him.

00:26:28.530 --> 00:26:33.250
For the unbelieving husband is sanctified by the wife,

00:26:33.570 --> 00:26:38.410
and the unbelieving wife is sanctified by the husband.

00:26:38.870 --> 00:26:43.810
Else were your children unclean, but now are they holy.

00:26:44.630 --> 00:26:48.750
But if the unbelieving depart, let him depart.

00:26:49.370 --> 00:26:54.430
A brother or a sister is not under bondage in such cases,

00:26:54.910 --> 00:26:57.950
but God hath called us to peace.

00:26:57.970 --> 00:27:03.310
For what knowest thou, O wife, whether thou shalt save thy husband?

00:27:03.890 --> 00:27:08.790
Or how knowest thou, O man, whether thou shalt save thy wife?

00:27:09.330 --> 00:27:15.670
But as God hath distributed to every man, as the Lord hath called everyone,

00:27:16.170 --> 00:27:20.550
so let him walk, and so ordain I in all churches.

00:27:21.170 --> 00:27:24.130
Is any man called being circumcised?

00:27:24.730 --> 00:27:27.510
Let him not become uncircumcised.

00:27:27.970 --> 00:27:31.170
Is any called in uncircumcision?

00:27:31.810 --> 00:27:34.290
Let him not be circumcised.

00:27:35.250 --> 00:27:39.530
Circumcision is nothing, and uncircumcision is nothing.

00:27:40.050 --> 00:27:43.390
But the keeping of the commandments of God,

00:27:43.870 --> 00:27:48.970
let every man abide in the same calling wherein he was called.

00:27:49.510 --> 00:27:51.670
Art thou called being a servant?

00:27:51.970 --> 00:27:57.550
Care not for it, but if thou mayest be made free, use it rather.

00:27:57.970 --> 00:28:03.990
For he that is called in the Lord being a servant is the Lord's free man.

00:28:04.570 --> 00:28:11.470
Likewise also, he that is called being free is Christ's servant.

00:28:12.290 --> 00:28:14.930
Ye are bought with a price.

00:28:15.630 --> 00:28:18.510
Be not ye the servants of men.

00:28:19.170 --> 00:28:24.990
Brethren, let every man wherein he is called, therein abide with God.

00:28:24.990 --> 00:28:29.770
Now, concerning versions, I have no commandment of the Lord,

00:28:30.170 --> 00:28:36.650
yet I give my judgment, as one that hath obtained mercy of the Lord to be faithful.

00:28:37.170 --> 00:28:42.530
I suppose, therefore, that this is good for the present distress.

00:28:43.110 --> 00:28:47.070
I say that it is good for a man so to be.

00:28:47.590 --> 00:28:49.650
Art thou bound unto a wife?

00:28:50.050 --> 00:28:51.930
Seek not to be loosed.

00:28:52.150 --> 00:28:54.010
Art thou loosed from a wife?

00:28:54.010 --> 00:28:56.230
Seek not a wife.

00:28:57.470 --> 00:29:01.770
But, and if thou marry, thou hast not sinned.

00:29:01.930 --> 00:29:05.930
And if aversion, marry, she hath not sinned.

00:29:05.990 --> 00:29:11.250
Nevertheless, such shall have trouble in the flesh, but I spare you.

00:29:11.770 --> 00:29:15.390
But, this I say, brethren, the time is short.

00:29:15.630 --> 00:29:21.470
It remaineth that both they that have wives be as though they had none,

00:29:21.470 --> 00:29:24.930
and they that weep as though they wept not,

00:29:25.470 --> 00:29:28.950
and they that rejoice as though they rejoiced not,

00:29:29.350 --> 00:29:33.550
and they that buy as though they possessed not,

00:29:33.690 --> 00:29:42.310
and they that use this world as not abusing it for the fashion of this world passeth away.

00:29:42.830 --> 00:29:47.590
But I would have you without carefulness.

00:29:47.590 --> 00:29:53.130
He that is unmarried careth for the things that belong to the Lord,

00:29:53.730 --> 00:29:56.210
how he may please the Lord.

00:29:56.550 --> 00:30:01.590
But he that is married careth for the things that are of the world,

00:30:01.890 --> 00:30:04.330
how he may please his wife.

00:30:04.950 --> 00:30:10.010
There is difference also between a wife and a virgin.

00:30:10.610 --> 00:30:14.150
The unmarried woman careth for the things of the Lord,

00:30:14.150 --> 00:30:18.870
that she may be holy both in body and in spirit.

00:30:19.550 --> 00:30:23.590
But she that is married careth for the things of the world,

00:30:24.010 --> 00:30:26.590
how she may please her husband.

00:30:27.270 --> 00:30:34.050
And this I speak for your own profit, not that I may cast a snare upon you,

00:30:34.350 --> 00:30:42.330
but for that which is comely and that ye may attend upon the Lord without distraction.

00:30:43.050 --> 00:30:51.010
But if any man think that he behaveeth himself uncumbly toward his virgin,

00:30:51.490 --> 00:30:55.590
if she pass the flower of her age and need so require,

00:30:56.110 --> 00:30:58.170
let him do what he will.

00:30:58.410 --> 00:31:01.070
He sinneth not, let them marry.

00:31:01.590 --> 00:31:06.130
Nevertheless, he that standeth steadfast in his heart,

00:31:06.370 --> 00:31:10.130
having no necessity but hath power over his own will,

00:31:10.130 --> 00:31:16.450
and hath so decreed in his heart that he will keep his virgin doeth well.

00:31:16.910 --> 00:31:20.610
So then, he that giveth her in marriage doeth well,

00:31:20.990 --> 00:31:24.610
but he that giveth her not in marriage doeth better.

00:31:25.370 --> 00:31:29.790
The wife is bound by the law as long as her husband liveth.

00:31:30.150 --> 00:31:37.070
But if her husband be dead, she is at liberty to be married to whom she will,

00:31:37.410 --> 00:31:39.030
only in the Lord.

00:31:39.650 --> 00:31:44.370
But she is happier if she so abide after my judgment,

00:31:44.770 --> 00:31:49.770
and I think also that I have the Spirit of God.

00:31:51.450 --> 00:31:52.810
Chapter 8

00:31:53.590 --> 00:31:59.970
Now, as touching things offered unto idols, we know that we all have knowledge.

00:32:01.310 --> 00:32:05.210
Knowledge puffeth up, but charity edifyeth.

00:32:05.210 --> 00:32:13.590
And if any man think that he knoweth anything, he knoweth nothing, yet as he ought to know.

00:32:14.210 --> 00:32:18.690
But if any man love God, the same is known of him.

00:32:19.750 --> 00:32:26.270
As concerning therefore the eating of those things that are offered in sacrifice unto idols,

00:32:26.710 --> 00:32:33.130
we know that an idol is nothing in the world, and that there is none other God but one.

00:32:33.590 --> 00:32:41.810
For though there be that are called gods, whether in heaven or in earth,

00:32:42.110 --> 00:32:45.250
as there be gods many, and lords many.

00:32:45.670 --> 00:32:52.910
But to us there is but one God, the Father of whom are all things, and we in him,

00:32:53.350 --> 00:33:01.810
and one Lord, Jesus Christ, by whom are all things, and we by him.

00:33:01.810 --> 00:33:05.930
Howbeit there is not in every man that knowledge.

00:33:06.390 --> 00:33:14.230
For some, with conscious of the idol, unto this hour eat it, as a thing offered unto an idol,

00:33:14.630 --> 00:33:17.890
and their conscious being weak is defiled.

00:33:19.110 --> 00:33:25.610
But me commendeth us not to God, for neither if we eat are we the better,

00:33:26.010 --> 00:33:29.870
neither if we eat not are we the worse.

00:33:30.430 --> 00:33:37.490
But take heed, lest by any means this liberty of yours become a stumbling block

00:33:37.490 --> 00:33:39.150
to them that are weak.

00:33:39.730 --> 00:33:46.550
For if any man see thee which hath knowledge sit at meat in the idol's temple,

00:33:46.970 --> 00:33:53.830
shall not the conscious of him which is weak be emboldened to eat those things which are offered

00:33:53.830 --> 00:33:54.870
to idols.

00:33:55.590 --> 00:34:02.750
And through thy knowledge shall the weak brother perish, for whom Christ died.

00:34:03.470 --> 00:34:13.970
But when ye sin so against the brethren, and wound their weak conscious, ye sin against Christ.

00:34:14.330 --> 00:34:23.510
Wherefore, if meat make my brother to offend, I will eat no flesh while the world standeth.

00:34:23.830 --> 00:34:26.570
Lest I make my brother to offend.

00:34:31.470 --> 00:34:34.670
Reading by Simon Wainwright.

00:34:36.670 --> 00:34:42.070
CHAPTERS IX and X of I Corinthians

00:35:04.730 --> 00:35:13.910
The first epistle of Paul to the Corinthians, King James Version, Chapter 9

00:35:13.910 --> 00:35:22.570
Am I not an apostle? Am I not free? Have I not seen Jesus Christ our Lord?

00:35:22.570 --> 00:35:26.590
Are not ye my work in the Lord?

00:35:27.370 --> 00:35:32.970
If I be not an apostle unto others, yet doubtless, I am to you,

00:35:33.190 --> 00:35:37.210
for the seal of mine apostleship are ye in the Lord.

00:35:37.950 --> 00:35:41.530
Mine answer to them that do examine me is this.

00:35:42.230 --> 00:35:45.470
Have we not power to eat and to drink?

00:35:45.470 --> 00:35:53.010
Have we not power to lead about a sister, a wife, as well as other apostles,

00:35:53.530 --> 00:35:57.870
and as the brethren of the Lord and Cephas?

00:35:58.630 --> 00:36:04.630
Or I only and Barnabas have not we power to forbear working?

00:36:05.270 --> 00:36:09.970
Who goeth a warfare any time at his own charges?

00:36:10.530 --> 00:36:14.130
Who planteth a vineyard and eateth not of the fruit thereof?

00:36:14.130 --> 00:36:19.750
Or who feedeth a flock and eateth not of the milk of the flock?

00:36:20.810 --> 00:36:23.630
Say I these things as a man?

00:36:24.410 --> 00:36:26.670
Or sayeth not the law the same also?

00:36:27.570 --> 00:36:30.150
For it is written in the law of Moses,

00:36:30.590 --> 00:36:35.010
Thou shalt not muzzle the mouth of the ox that treadeth out the corn.

00:36:35.850 --> 00:36:38.810
Doth God take care for oxen?

00:36:39.310 --> 00:36:42.850
Or sayeth he it altogether for our sakes?

00:36:42.850 --> 00:36:45.250
For our sakes, no doubt.

00:36:45.710 --> 00:36:50.490
This is written that he that ploweth should plow in hope,

00:36:51.370 --> 00:36:57.530
and that he that thresheth in hope should be partaker of his hope.

00:36:57.990 --> 00:37:01.530
If we have sown unto you spiritual things,

00:37:02.190 --> 00:37:06.830
is it a great thing if we shall reap your carnal things?

00:37:06.830 --> 00:37:11.730
If others be partakers of this power over you,

00:37:12.170 --> 00:37:14.110
are not we rather, nevertheless,

00:37:14.890 --> 00:37:18.600
we have not used this power but suffer all things,

00:37:19.370 --> 00:37:22.490
lest we should hinder the gospel of Christ?

00:37:23.110 --> 00:37:28.270
Do ye not know that they which minister about holy things

00:37:28.270 --> 00:37:30.550
live of the things of the temple,

00:37:30.750 --> 00:37:35.290
and they which wait at the altar are partakers with the altar?

00:37:36.110 --> 00:37:39.070
Even so have the Lord ordained

00:37:39.070 --> 00:37:43.830
that they which preach the gospel should live of the gospel.

00:37:44.430 --> 00:37:47.210
But I have used none of these things,

00:37:47.330 --> 00:37:49.190
neither have I written these things,

00:37:49.630 --> 00:37:51.970
that it should be so done unto me.

00:37:52.610 --> 00:37:55.830
For it were better for me to die

00:37:55.830 --> 00:37:59.870
than that any man should make my glorying void.

00:38:01.230 --> 00:38:03.070
For though I preach the gospel,

00:38:03.070 --> 00:38:05.450
I have nothing to glory of.

00:38:06.130 --> 00:38:08.650
For necessity is laid upon me,

00:38:08.890 --> 00:38:13.490
yea, woe is unto me if I preach not the gospel.

00:38:14.170 --> 00:38:16.630
For if I do this thing willingly,

00:38:17.090 --> 00:38:18.310
I have a reward.

00:38:18.690 --> 00:38:20.730
But if against my will,

00:38:21.210 --> 00:38:24.930
a dispensation of the gospel is committed unto me.

00:38:25.530 --> 00:38:27.650
What is my reward then?

00:38:27.890 --> 00:38:31.410
Verily, that when I preach the gospel,

00:38:31.410 --> 00:38:34.610
I may make the gospel of Christ without charge,

00:38:35.110 --> 00:38:38.490
that I abuse not my power in the gospel.

00:38:38.810 --> 00:38:41.810
For though I be free from all men,

00:38:41.970 --> 00:38:45.590
yet have I made myself servant unto all,

00:38:45.850 --> 00:38:47.610
that I might gain the more.

00:38:47.970 --> 00:38:52.770
And unto the Jews I became as a Jew,

00:38:53.450 --> 00:38:55.650
that I might gain the Jews

00:38:55.650 --> 00:38:58.590
to them that are under the law,

00:38:59.010 --> 00:39:00.570
as under the law,

00:39:00.570 --> 00:39:03.970
that I might gain them that are under the law,

00:39:04.330 --> 00:39:07.730
to them that are without law as without law,

00:39:08.230 --> 00:39:10.590
being not without law to God,

00:39:10.990 --> 00:39:13.010
but under the law to Christ,

00:39:13.330 --> 00:39:18.090
that I might gain them that are without law.

00:39:18.950 --> 00:39:21.490
To the weak became I as weak,

00:39:21.790 --> 00:39:23.470
that I might gain the weak.

00:39:23.770 --> 00:39:27.270
I am made all things to all men,

00:39:27.270 --> 00:39:31.630
that I might by all means save some.

00:39:32.310 --> 00:39:34.650
And this I do for the gospel's sake,

00:39:34.910 --> 00:39:38.070
that I might be partaker thereof with you.

00:39:38.550 --> 00:39:42.690
Know ye not that they which run in a race run all,

00:39:42.990 --> 00:39:45.070
but one receiveth the prize?

00:39:45.570 --> 00:39:48.430
So run, that ye may obtain.

00:39:48.990 --> 00:39:52.550
And every man that striveth for the mastery

00:39:52.550 --> 00:39:55.770
is temperate in all things.

00:39:55.770 --> 00:40:00.010
Now, they do it to obtain a corruptible crown,

00:40:00.590 --> 00:40:03.410
but we in incorruptible.

00:40:04.170 --> 00:40:05.710
I therefore so run,

00:40:06.310 --> 00:40:08.370
not as uncertainly,

00:40:08.690 --> 00:40:09.730
so fight I,

00:40:10.010 --> 00:40:13.210
not as one that beateth the air.

00:40:13.490 --> 00:40:16.090
But I keep under my body

00:40:16.090 --> 00:40:19.290
and bring it into subjection,

00:40:19.530 --> 00:40:21.770
lest that by any means,

00:40:22.150 --> 00:40:24.070
when I have preached to others,

00:40:24.070 --> 00:40:27.570
I myself should be a cast away.

00:40:30.530 --> 00:40:31.910
Moreover, brethren,

00:40:32.330 --> 00:40:35.150
I would not that ye should be ignorant

00:40:35.150 --> 00:40:39.870
how that all our fathers were under the cloud

00:40:39.870 --> 00:40:42.510
and all passed through the sea,

00:40:42.810 --> 00:40:46.510
and were all baptized unto Moses in the cloud

00:40:46.510 --> 00:40:48.030
and in the sea,

00:40:48.350 --> 00:40:51.710
and did all eat the same spiritual meat,

00:40:51.710 --> 00:40:55.770
and did all drink of the same spiritual drink,

00:40:56.130 --> 00:40:58.670
for they drank of that spiritual rock

00:40:58.670 --> 00:41:00.350
that followed them,

00:41:00.630 --> 00:41:02.670
and that rock was Christ.

00:41:02.990 --> 00:41:07.530
But with many of them God was not well pleased,

00:41:07.810 --> 00:41:10.670
for they were overthrown in the wilderness.

00:41:11.170 --> 00:41:14.590
Now, these things were our examples

00:41:14.590 --> 00:41:19.830
to the intent we should not lust after evil things,

00:41:19.830 --> 00:41:22.050
as they also lusted.

00:41:22.490 --> 00:41:24.830
Neither be ye idolers,

00:41:26.110 --> 00:41:27.810
as were some of them,

00:41:27.930 --> 00:41:29.050
as it is written,

00:41:29.490 --> 00:41:32.130
the people sat down to eat and drink

00:41:32.130 --> 00:41:34.190
and rose up to play.

00:41:34.750 --> 00:41:37.110
Neither let us commit fornication

00:41:37.110 --> 00:41:38.670
as some of them committed

00:41:38.670 --> 00:41:41.030
and fell in one day,

00:41:41.230 --> 00:41:43.130
three in twenty thousand.

00:41:43.610 --> 00:41:45.550
Neither let us tempt Christ,

00:41:45.910 --> 00:41:47.990
as some of them also tempted

00:41:47.990 --> 00:41:51.010
and were destroyed of serpents.

00:41:51.290 --> 00:41:52.510
Neither murmur ye,

00:41:52.590 --> 00:41:55.390
as some of them also murmured

00:41:55.390 --> 00:41:58.410
and were destroyed of the destroyer.

00:41:58.690 --> 00:42:02.150
Now, all these things happened unto them

00:42:02.150 --> 00:42:03.370
for in samples,

00:42:03.790 --> 00:42:07.930
and they are written for our admonition

00:42:07.930 --> 00:42:11.210
upon whom the ends of the world are come.

00:42:12.110 --> 00:42:15.630
Wherefore, let him that thinketh he standeth

00:42:15.630 --> 00:42:17.810
take heed, lest he fall.

00:42:18.310 --> 00:42:21.190
There hath no temptation taken you,

00:42:21.350 --> 00:42:23.970
but such as is common to man.

00:42:24.510 --> 00:42:25.830
But God is faithful,

00:42:26.390 --> 00:42:28.770
who will not suffer you to be tempted

00:42:28.770 --> 00:42:31.050
above that ye are able.

00:42:31.650 --> 00:42:33.890
But will with the temptation

00:42:33.890 --> 00:42:36.890
also make a way to escape,

00:42:37.250 --> 00:42:39.350
that ye may be able to bear it.

00:42:39.870 --> 00:42:41.830
Wherefore, my dearly beloved,

00:42:41.990 --> 00:42:43.570
flee from idol-tree.

00:42:43.570 --> 00:42:46.770
I speak as to wise men,

00:42:46.970 --> 00:42:48.850
judge ye what I say.

00:42:49.430 --> 00:42:51.730
The cup of blessing which we bless,

00:42:52.030 --> 00:42:53.810
is it not the communion

00:42:53.810 --> 00:42:55.250
of the blood of Christ?

00:42:55.790 --> 00:42:57.370
The bread which we break,

00:42:57.850 --> 00:42:59.590
is it not the communion

00:42:59.590 --> 00:43:01.570
of the body of Christ?

00:43:02.210 --> 00:43:05.770
For we being many are one bread

00:43:05.770 --> 00:43:07.530
and one body,

00:43:07.890 --> 00:43:10.730
for we are all partakers of

00:43:10.730 --> 00:43:11.970
that one bread.

00:43:11.970 --> 00:43:15.070
Behold, Israel after the flesh,

00:43:15.590 --> 00:43:17.650
are not they which eat

00:43:17.650 --> 00:43:19.200
of the sacrifices partaker

00:43:19.510 --> 00:43:20.270
of the altar?

00:43:21.190 --> 00:43:22.470
What say I then,

00:43:22.910 --> 00:43:24.790
that the idol is anything,

00:43:25.110 --> 00:43:26.810
or that which is offered

00:43:26.810 --> 00:43:29.470
in sacrifice to idols is anything?

00:43:30.250 --> 00:43:32.670
But I say, that the things

00:43:32.670 --> 00:43:34.470
which the Gentiles sacrifice,

00:43:34.650 --> 00:43:36.310
they sacrifice to devils

00:43:36.310 --> 00:43:37.470
and not to God.

00:43:37.870 --> 00:43:39.910
And I would not that ye

00:43:39.910 --> 00:43:41.670
should have fellowship

00:43:41.670 --> 00:43:43.770
with devils.

00:43:44.030 --> 00:43:46.330
Ye cannot drink the cup of the Lord

00:43:46.330 --> 00:43:48.170
and the cup of devils.

00:43:48.490 --> 00:43:50.130
Ye cannot be partakers

00:43:50.130 --> 00:43:51.710
of the Lord's table

00:43:51.710 --> 00:43:54.870
and of the table of devils.

00:43:55.330 --> 00:43:56.870
Do we provoke the Lord

00:43:56.870 --> 00:43:57.750
to jealousy?

00:43:58.610 --> 00:43:59.990
Are we stronger than he?

00:44:00.630 --> 00:44:02.610
All things are lawful for me,

00:44:02.770 --> 00:44:05.390
but all things are not expedient.

00:44:05.930 --> 00:44:08.130
All things are lawful for me,

00:44:08.130 --> 00:44:10.390
but all things edified not.

00:44:10.930 --> 00:44:12.850
Let no man seek his own,

00:44:13.170 --> 00:44:15.770
but every man another's wealth.

00:44:16.430 --> 00:44:19.390
Whatsoever is sold in the shambles

00:44:19.390 --> 00:44:20.750
that eat,

00:44:21.050 --> 00:44:23.850
asking no question for conscious sake.

00:44:24.490 --> 00:44:27.190
For the earth is the Lord's

00:44:27.190 --> 00:44:28.990
and the fullness thereof.

00:44:29.390 --> 00:44:31.910
If any of them that believe not

00:44:31.910 --> 00:44:33.550
bid you to a feast

00:44:33.790 --> 00:44:35.770
and ye be disposed to go,

00:44:35.770 --> 00:44:38.870
whatsoever is set before you eat,

00:44:39.010 --> 00:44:41.170
asking no question for conscious sake.

00:44:41.710 --> 00:44:44.450
But if any man say unto you,

00:44:44.710 --> 00:44:47.870
this is offered in sacrifice unto idols,

00:44:48.370 --> 00:44:51.850
eat not, for his sake that showed it,

00:44:52.010 --> 00:44:53.490
and for conscious sake.

00:44:53.890 --> 00:44:55.850
For the earth is the Lord's

00:44:55.850 --> 00:44:57.310
and the fullness thereof.

00:44:57.910 --> 00:44:59.470
Conscious I say,

00:44:59.910 --> 00:45:02.730
not thine own, but of the other.

00:45:02.730 --> 00:45:05.630
For why is my liberty judged

00:45:05.630 --> 00:45:07.650
of another man's conscious?

00:45:08.030 --> 00:45:11.550
For if I by grace be a partaker,

00:45:12.210 --> 00:45:14.750
why am I evil spoken of

00:45:14.750 --> 00:45:18.170
for that for which I give thanks?

00:45:18.830 --> 00:45:21.830
Whether therefore ye eat or drink

00:45:21.830 --> 00:45:23.810
or whatsoever ye do,

00:45:24.130 --> 00:45:27.290
do all to the glory of God.

00:45:27.770 --> 00:45:29.810
Give none offense,

00:45:29.810 --> 00:45:33.070
neither to the Jews, nor to the Gentiles,

00:45:33.250 --> 00:45:35.650
nor to the Church of God.

00:45:35.930 --> 00:45:39.910
Even as I please all men in all things,

00:45:40.410 --> 00:45:42.250
not seeking mine own,

00:45:42.430 --> 00:45:44.950
profit but the profit of many,

00:45:45.470 --> 00:45:48.010
that they may be saved.

00:46:13.630 --> 00:46:18.430
Be ye followers of me, even as I also am of Christ.

00:46:18.430 --> 00:46:24.250
Now I praise you, brethren, that ye remember me in all things, and keep the ordinances,

00:46:24.450 --> 00:46:26.510
as I have delivered them to you.

00:46:26.970 --> 00:46:32.150
But I would have you know, that the head of every man is Christ, and the head of the woman

00:46:32.150 --> 00:46:35.270
is the man, and the head of Christ is God.

00:46:35.770 --> 00:46:41.270
Every man praying or prophesying, having his head covered, dishonoreth his head.

00:46:41.690 --> 00:46:47.250
But every woman that prayeth or prophesieth with her head uncovered, dishonoreth her head.

00:46:47.250 --> 00:46:51.530
For that is even all one, as if she were shaven.

00:46:51.970 --> 00:46:55.570
For if the woman be not covered, let her also be shorn.

00:46:55.970 --> 00:47:00.550
But if it be a shame for a woman to be shorn or shaven, let her be covered.

00:47:01.310 --> 00:47:06.530
For a man indeed ought not to cover his head, for as much as he is the image and glory of

00:47:06.530 --> 00:47:10.210
God, but the woman is the glory of the man.

00:47:10.890 --> 00:47:14.530
For the man is not of the woman, but the woman of the man.

00:47:14.970 --> 00:47:18.750
Neither was the man created for the woman, but the woman for the man.

00:47:19.190 --> 00:47:24.810
For this cause ought the woman to have power on her head because of the angels.

00:47:25.670 --> 00:47:31.030
Nevertheless, neither is the man without the woman, neither the woman without the man in

00:47:31.030 --> 00:47:31.570
the Lord.

00:47:32.130 --> 00:47:38.650
For as the woman is of the man, even so the man also by the woman, but all things of God.

00:47:38.650 --> 00:47:43.490
Judge in yourselves, is it comely that a woman pray into God uncovered?

00:47:44.490 --> 00:47:49.970
Doth not even nature itself teach you that if a man have long hair it is a shame to him?

00:47:50.630 --> 00:47:57.310
But if a woman have long hair, it is a glory to her, for her hair is given her for a covering.

00:47:58.010 --> 00:48:03.890
But if any man seem to be contentious, we have no such custom, neither the churches

00:48:03.890 --> 00:48:04.550
of God.

00:48:05.590 --> 00:48:12.030
Now in this that I declare unto you, I praise you not, that ye come together not for the

00:48:12.030 --> 00:48:13.610
better, but for the worse.

00:48:14.510 --> 00:48:19.290
For first of all, when ye come together in the church, I hear that there be divisions

00:48:19.290 --> 00:48:21.550
among you, and I partly believe it.

00:48:22.090 --> 00:48:28.090
For there must be also heresies among you, that they which are approved may be made manifest

00:48:28.090 --> 00:48:29.070
among you.

00:48:29.770 --> 00:48:34.790
When ye come together therefore into one place, this is not to eat the Lord's supper.

00:48:35.970 --> 00:48:42.410
For in eating every one taketh before other his own supper, and one is hungry, and another

00:48:42.410 --> 00:48:43.210
is drunken.

00:48:43.990 --> 00:48:48.050
What have ye not houses to eat and to drink in?

00:48:48.570 --> 00:48:52.810
Or despise ye the church of God, and shame them that have not?

00:48:53.630 --> 00:48:55.650
What shall I say to you?

00:48:55.910 --> 00:48:57.430
Shall I praise you in this?

00:48:57.430 --> 00:48:59.550
I praise you not.

00:49:00.270 --> 00:49:06.750
For I have received of the Lord that which also I delivered unto you, that the Lord Jesus,

00:49:07.070 --> 00:49:10.230
the same night in which he was betrayed, took bread.

00:49:10.870 --> 00:49:15.250
And when he had given thanks, he break it, and said, Take eat.

00:49:15.710 --> 00:49:18.990
This is my body, which is broken for you.

00:49:19.690 --> 00:49:21.730
This do in remembrance of me.

00:49:22.430 --> 00:49:28.250
After the same manner also, he took the cup when he had supped, saying, This cup is the

00:49:28.250 --> 00:49:30.350
New Testament in my blood.

00:49:31.010 --> 00:49:35.210
This do ye as oft as ye drink it in remembrance of me.

00:49:35.690 --> 00:49:41.590
For as often as ye eat this bread and drink this cup, ye do show the Lord's death till

00:49:41.590 --> 00:49:42.150
he come.

00:49:43.170 --> 00:49:48.090
Wherefore whosoever shall eat this bread and drink this cup of the Lord unworthily shall

00:49:48.090 --> 00:49:51.210
be guilty of the body and blood of the Lord.

00:49:52.010 --> 00:49:57.670
But let a man examine himself, and so let him eat of that bread and drink of that cup.

00:49:58.490 --> 00:50:04.130
For he that eateth and drinketh unworthily eateth and drinketh damnation to himself,

00:50:04.550 --> 00:50:06.270
not discerning the Lord's body.

00:50:06.930 --> 00:50:11.430
For this cause many are weak and sickly among you, and many sleep.

00:50:12.230 --> 00:50:15.590
For if we would judge ourselves, we should not be judged.

00:50:16.470 --> 00:50:21.870
But when we are judged, we are chastened of the Lord, that we should not be condemned

00:50:21.870 --> 00:50:22.930
with the world.

00:50:23.810 --> 00:50:28.310
Wherefore, my brethren, when ye come together to eat, tarry one for another.

00:50:28.890 --> 00:50:35.190
And if any man hunger, let him eat at home, that ye come not together unto condemnation.

00:50:35.590 --> 00:50:38.590
And the rest I will set in order when I come.

00:50:39.090 --> 00:50:40.510
Chapter 12

00:50:40.510 --> 00:50:44.870
Now concerning spiritual gifts, brethren, I would not have you ignorant.

00:50:45.930 --> 00:50:52.410
Ye know that ye were Gentiles carried away unto these dumb idols, even as ye were led.

00:50:53.090 --> 00:50:58.950
Wherefore I give you to understand that no man speaking by the Spirit of God calleth

00:50:58.950 --> 00:51:05.290
Jesus accursed, and that no man can say that Jesus is the Lord, but by the Holy Ghost.

00:51:05.850 --> 00:51:09.730
Now there are diversities of gifts, but the same Spirit.

00:51:10.370 --> 00:51:13.870
And there are differences of administrations, but the same Lord.

00:51:14.490 --> 00:51:20.550
And there are diversities of operations, but it is the same God which worketh all in all.

00:51:21.330 --> 00:51:26.690
But the manifestation of the Spirit is given to every man to profit withal.

00:51:27.590 --> 00:51:32.710
For to one is given by the Spirit the word of wisdom, to another the word of knowledge

00:51:32.710 --> 00:51:38.310
by the same Spirit, to another faith by the same Spirit, to another the gifts of healing

00:51:38.310 --> 00:51:45.050
by the same Spirit, to another the working of miracles, to another prophecy, to another

00:51:45.050 --> 00:51:51.930
discerning of spirits, to another diverse kinds of tongues, to another the interpretation

00:51:51.930 --> 00:51:52.630
of tongues.

00:51:53.530 --> 00:52:01.270
But all these worketh that one and the self same Spirit, dividing to every man severally

00:52:01.270 --> 00:52:02.050
as he will.

00:52:02.730 --> 00:52:08.430
For as the body is one, and hath many members, and all the members of that one body being

00:52:08.430 --> 00:52:12.430
many are one body, so also is Christ.

00:52:13.090 --> 00:52:19.090
For by one Spirit we are all baptized into one body, whether we be Jews or Gentiles,

00:52:19.410 --> 00:52:24.890
whether we be bond or free, and have been all made to drink into one Spirit.

00:52:25.410 --> 00:52:28.210
For the body is not one member, but many.

00:52:28.690 --> 00:52:35.030
If the foot shall say, Because I am not the hand, I am not of the body, Is it therefore

00:52:35.030 --> 00:52:36.150
not of the body?

00:52:36.750 --> 00:52:43.370
And if the ear shall say, Because I am not the eye, I am not of the body, Is it therefore

00:52:43.370 --> 00:52:44.430
not of the body?

00:52:44.990 --> 00:52:48.150
If the whole body were an eye, where were the hearing?

00:52:48.930 --> 00:52:52.210
If the whole were hearing, where were the smelling?

00:52:52.210 --> 00:52:58.270
But now hath God set the members, every one of them, in the body, as it hath pleased him.

00:52:58.730 --> 00:53:02.170
And if they were all one member, where were the body?

00:53:02.710 --> 00:53:06.550
But now are they many members, yet but one body.

00:53:07.310 --> 00:53:12.650
And the eye cannot say unto the hand, I have no need of thee, nor again the head to the

00:53:12.650 --> 00:53:14.810
feet, I have no need of you.

00:53:15.570 --> 00:53:21.670
Nay, much more those members of the body which seem to be more feeble are necessary.

00:53:22.410 --> 00:53:28.890
And those members of the body which we think to be less honourable, upon these we bestow

00:53:28.890 --> 00:53:30.170
more abundant honour.

00:53:30.790 --> 00:53:34.750
And our uncomely parts have more abundant comeliness.

00:53:35.790 --> 00:53:42.030
For our comely parts have no need, but God hath tempered the body together, having given

00:53:42.030 --> 00:53:44.990
more abundant honour to that part which lacked.

00:53:45.810 --> 00:53:50.310
That there should be no schism in the body, but that the members should have the same

00:53:50.310 --> 00:53:52.010
care one for another.

00:53:53.190 --> 00:53:57.250
And whether one member suffer, all the members suffer with it.

00:53:57.550 --> 00:54:01.630
Or when member be honoured, all the members rejoice with it.

00:54:01.990 --> 00:54:06.190
Now ye are the body of Christ, and members in particular.

00:54:06.190 --> 00:54:13.710
And God hath set some in the church, first apostles, secondarily prophets, thirdly teachers,

00:54:14.230 --> 00:54:21.390
after that miracles, then gifts of healings, helps, governments, diversities of tongues.

00:54:22.110 --> 00:54:23.370
Are all apostles?

00:54:23.710 --> 00:54:24.610
Are all prophets?

00:54:24.950 --> 00:54:25.870
Are all teachers?

00:54:26.330 --> 00:54:28.090
Are all workers of miracles?

00:54:28.690 --> 00:54:30.110
Have all the gifts of healing?

00:54:30.670 --> 00:54:32.190
Do all speak with tongues?

00:54:32.830 --> 00:54:34.090
Do all interpret?

00:54:34.090 --> 00:54:42.450
But covet earnestly the best gifts, and yet show I unto you a more excellent way.

00:54:52.990 --> 00:54:53.510
13.

00:55:05.370 --> 00:55:11.190
Though I speak with the tongues of men and of angels, and have not charity, I am become

00:55:11.790 --> 00:55:18.210
brass, or a tinkling symbol. And though I have the gift of prophecy, and understand all mysteries,

00:55:18.310 --> 00:55:23.230
and all knowledge, and though I have all faith, so that I could remove mountains,

00:55:23.730 --> 00:55:30.410
and have not charity, I am nothing. And though I bestow all my goods to feed the poor, and though

00:55:30.410 --> 00:55:38.250
I give my body to be burned, and have not charity, it profiteth me nothing. Charity suffereth long,

00:55:38.250 --> 00:55:46.750
and is kind. Charity envyeth not. Charity vaunteth not itself, it is not puffed up, doth not behave

00:55:46.750 --> 00:55:54.310
itself unseemly, seeketh not her own, is not easily provoked, thinketh no evil. Rejoiceth

00:55:54.310 --> 00:56:00.350
not in iniquity, but rejoiceth in the truth. Beareth all things, believeth all things,

00:56:00.730 --> 00:56:07.910
hopeth all things, endureth all things. Charity never faileth, but whether there be prophecies,

00:56:07.910 --> 00:56:14.010
they shall fail, whether there be tongues, they shall cease, whether there be knowledge,

00:56:14.110 --> 00:56:20.910
it shall vanish away. For we know in part, and we prophesy in part, but when that which is perfect

00:56:20.910 --> 00:56:27.830
is come, then that which is in part shall be done away. When I was a child, I spake as a child,

00:56:27.910 --> 00:56:35.030
I understood as a child, I thought as a child, but when I became a man, I put away childish things.

00:56:35.030 --> 00:56:43.410
For now we see through a glass darkly, but then face to face. Now I know in part, but then I shall

00:56:43.410 --> 00:56:51.210
know even as also I am known. And now abideth faith, hope, charity, these three, but the

00:56:51.210 --> 00:56:54.950
greatest of these is charity. CHAPTER XIV

00:56:55.610 --> 00:57:02.770
Follow after charity and desire spiritual gifts, but rather that ye may prophesy. For he that

00:57:02.770 --> 00:57:09.670
speaketh in an unknown tongue speaketh not unto men, but unto God. For no man understandeth him,

00:57:09.950 --> 00:57:17.230
howbeit in the spirit he speaketh mysteries. But he that prophesieth speaketh unto men to edification

00:57:17.230 --> 00:57:24.270
and exhortation and comfort. He that speaketh in an unknown tongue edifyeth himself,

00:57:24.730 --> 00:57:30.590
but he that prophesieth edifyeth the church. I would that ye all speak with tongues,

00:57:30.590 --> 00:57:36.670
but rather that ye prophesied. For greater is he that prophesieth than he that speaketh with

00:57:36.670 --> 00:57:43.950
tongues, except he interpret that the church may receive edifying. Now brethren, if I come unto you

00:57:43.950 --> 00:57:49.930
speaking with tongues, what shall I profit you, except I shall speak to you either by revelation

00:57:49.930 --> 00:57:57.010
or by knowledge or by prophesying or by doctrine? And even things without life giving sound,

00:57:57.010 --> 00:58:02.650
whether pipe or harp, except they have a distinction in the sounds, how shall it be

00:58:02.650 --> 00:58:09.450
known what is piped or harped? If the trumpet give an uncertain sound, who shall prepare himself to

00:58:09.450 --> 00:58:15.950
the battle? So likewise ye, except ye utter by the tongue words easy to be understood,

00:58:16.450 --> 00:58:23.710
how shall it be known what is spoken? For ye shall speak into the air. There are, it may be,

00:58:23.710 --> 00:58:29.950
so many kinds of voices in the world, and none of them is without signification. Therefore,

00:58:30.090 --> 00:58:35.730
if I know not the meaning of the voice, I shall be unto him that speaketh a barbarian,

00:58:36.010 --> 00:58:42.650
and he that speaketh shall be a barbarian unto me. Even so ye, for as much as ye are

00:58:42.650 --> 00:58:48.130
zealous of spiritual gifts, seek that ye may excel to the edifying of the church.

00:58:48.850 --> 00:58:55.690
Wherefore, let him that speaketh in an unknown tongue pray that he may interpret. For if I pray

00:58:55.690 --> 00:59:02.730
in an unknown tongue, my spirit prayeth, but my understanding is unfruitful. What is it then?

00:59:02.730 --> 00:59:08.650
I will pray with the spirit, and I will pray with the understanding also. I will sing with

00:59:08.650 --> 00:59:15.450
the spirit, and I will sing with the understanding also. Else when thou shalt bless with the spirit,

00:59:15.450 --> 00:59:21.270
how shall he that occupieth the room of the unlearned say Amen at thy giving of thanks,

00:59:21.570 --> 00:59:28.670
seeing he understandeth not what thou sayest? For thou verily givest thanks well, but the other

00:59:28.670 --> 00:59:35.670
is not edified. I thank my God I speak with tongues more than ye all. Yet in the church

00:59:35.670 --> 00:59:42.270
I had rather speak five words with my understanding, that by my voice I might teach others also,

00:59:42.270 --> 00:59:48.750
than ten thousand words in an unknown tongue. Brethren, be not children in understanding,

00:59:49.250 --> 00:59:56.130
howbeit in malice be ye children, but in understanding be men. In the law it is written,

00:59:56.410 --> 01:00:02.330
with men of other tongues and other lips will I speak unto this people, and yet for all that

01:00:02.330 --> 01:00:09.470
will they not hear me, saith the Lord. Wherefore, tongues are for a sign, not to them that believe,

01:00:09.470 --> 01:00:15.350
but to them that believe not. But prophesying serveth not for them that believe not,

01:00:15.510 --> 01:00:21.370
but for them which believe. If therefore the whole church be come together into one place,

01:00:21.710 --> 01:00:26.790
and all speak with tongues, and there come in those that are unlearned or unbelievers,

01:00:27.210 --> 01:00:33.370
will they not say that ye are mad? But if all prophesy, and there come in one that believeth

01:00:33.370 --> 01:00:39.810
not, or one unlearned, he is convinced of all, he is judged of all. And thus are the

01:00:39.810 --> 01:00:45.710
secrets of his heart made manifest, and so falling down on his face he will worship God,

01:00:46.090 --> 01:00:52.550
and report that God is in you of a truth. How is it then, brethren, when ye come together,

01:00:52.750 --> 01:00:58.070
every one of you hath a psalm, hath a doctrine, hath a tongue, hath a revelation,

01:00:58.070 --> 01:01:06.150
hath an interpretation? Let all things be done unto edifying. If any man speak in an unknown tongue,

01:01:06.530 --> 01:01:12.710
let it be by two, or at the most by three, and that by course, and let one interpret.

01:01:13.230 --> 01:01:18.870
But if there be no interpreter, let him keep silence in the church, and let him speak to

01:01:18.870 --> 01:01:26.470
himself and to God. Let the prophets speak two or three, and let the other judge. If anything be

01:01:26.470 --> 01:01:33.950
veiled to another that sitteth by, let the first hold his peace. For ye may all prophesy one by one

01:01:33.950 --> 01:01:39.750
that all may learn, and all may be comforted. And the spirits of the prophets are subject

01:01:39.750 --> 01:01:46.110
to the prophets. For God is not the author of confusion, but of peace, as in all churches of

01:01:46.110 --> 01:01:52.630
the saints. Let your women keep silence in the churches, for it is not permitted unto them to

01:01:52.630 --> 01:01:59.430
speak. But they are commanded to be under obedience, as also saith the law. And if they will learn

01:01:59.430 --> 01:02:05.450
anything, let them ask their husbands at home, for it is a shame for women to speak in the church.

01:02:05.990 --> 01:02:13.470
What, came the word of God out from you, or came it unto you only? If any man think himself to be a

01:02:13.470 --> 01:02:18.710
prophet, or spiritual, let him acknowledge that the things I write unto you are the commandments

01:02:18.710 --> 01:02:26.810
of the Lord. But if any man be ignorant, let him be ignorant. Wherefore, brethren, covet to prophesy,

01:02:27.110 --> 01:02:33.130
and forbid not to speak with tongues. Let all things be done decently and in order.

01:02:56.790 --> 01:03:03.870
15 I declare unto you the Gospel which I preached unto you, which also ye have received, and

01:03:03.870 --> 01:03:10.490
wherein ye stand, by which also ye are saved, if ye keep in memory what I preached unto

01:03:10.490 --> 01:03:13.230
you, unless ye have believed in vain.

01:03:13.690 --> 01:03:19.290
For I delivered unto you, first of all, that which I also received, how that Christ died

01:03:19.290 --> 01:03:24.430
for our sins according to the Scriptures, and that He was buried, and that He rose again

01:03:24.430 --> 01:03:29.570
the third day according to the Scriptures, and that He was seen of Cephas, then of the

01:03:30.250 --> 01:03:36.530
After that, He was seen of above five hundred brethren at once, of whom the greater part

01:03:36.530 --> 01:03:40.330
remain unto this present, but some are fallen asleep.

01:03:40.830 --> 01:03:44.950
After that, He was seen of James, then of all the apostles.

01:03:45.350 --> 01:03:50.870
And last of all, He was seen of me also, as of one born out of due time.

01:03:51.270 --> 01:03:57.090
For I am the least of the apostles, that am not meet to be called an apostle, because

01:03:57.090 --> 01:03:59.130
I persecuted the Church of God.

01:03:59.690 --> 01:04:06.330
But by the grace of God I am what I am, and His grace which was bestowed upon me was not

01:04:06.330 --> 01:04:12.730
in vain, but I labored more abundantly than they all, yet not I, but the grace of God

01:04:12.730 --> 01:04:13.990
which was with me.

01:04:14.690 --> 01:04:19.990
Therefore, whether it were I or they, so we preach, and so ye believed.

01:04:20.610 --> 01:04:26.110
Now if Christ be preached, that He rose from the dead, how say some among you, that there

01:04:26.110 --> 01:04:27.930
is no resurrection of the dead?

01:04:28.330 --> 01:04:32.690
But if there be no resurrection of the dead, then is Christ not risen.

01:04:33.070 --> 01:04:39.070
And if Christ be not risen, then is our preaching vain, and your faith is also vain.

01:04:39.610 --> 01:04:45.250
Yea, and we are found false witnesses of God, because we have testified of God that He raised

01:04:45.250 --> 01:04:50.370
up Christ, whom He raised not up, if so be that the dead rise not.

01:04:50.950 --> 01:04:54.610
For if the dead rise not, then is not Christ raised.

01:04:54.910 --> 01:05:00.090
And if Christ be not raised, your faith is vain, ye are yet in your sins.

01:05:00.690 --> 01:05:04.570
Then they also which are fallen asleep in Christ are perished.

01:05:05.110 --> 01:05:10.990
If in this life only we have hope in Christ, then we are of all men most miserable.

01:05:11.830 --> 01:05:17.170
But now is Christ risen from the dead, and become the firstfruits of them that slept.

01:05:17.630 --> 01:05:22.850
For since by man came death, by man came also the resurrection of the dead.

01:05:22.850 --> 01:05:28.890
For as in Adam all die, even so in Christ shall all be made alive.

01:05:29.370 --> 01:05:35.630
But every man in his own order, Christ the firstfruits, afterward they that are Christ's

01:05:35.630 --> 01:05:36.530
at his coming.

01:05:37.230 --> 01:05:43.590
Then cometh the end, when he shall have delivered up the kingdom to God, even the Father, when

01:05:43.590 --> 01:05:47.510
he shall have put down all rule and all authority and power.

01:05:48.100 --> 01:05:52.410
For he must reign till he hath put all enemies under his feet.

01:05:52.990 --> 01:05:56.190
The last enemy that shall be destroyed is death.

01:05:56.730 --> 01:05:59.250
For he hath put all things under his feet.

01:05:59.690 --> 01:06:05.870
But when he saith all things are put under him, it is manifest that he is accepted which

01:06:05.870 --> 01:06:07.710
did put all things under him.

01:06:08.150 --> 01:06:14.410
And when all things shall be subdued unto him, then shall the Son also Himself be subject

01:06:14.410 --> 01:06:19.290
unto him that put all things under him, that God may be all in all.

01:06:20.070 --> 01:06:25.410
Else what shall they do, which are baptized for the dead, if the dead rise not at all?

01:06:25.730 --> 01:06:28.070
Why are they then baptized for the dead?

01:06:28.470 --> 01:06:31.570
And why stand we in jeopardy every hour?

01:06:32.390 --> 01:06:38.370
I protest by your rejoicing, which I have in Christ Jesus our Lord, I die daily.

01:06:38.890 --> 01:06:45.070
If after the manner of men I have fought with beasts at Ephesus, what advantageeth it me,

01:06:45.330 --> 01:06:46.710
if the dead rise not?

01:06:47.190 --> 01:06:49.870
Let us eat and drink, for to-morrow we die.

01:06:50.570 --> 01:06:54.530
Be not deceived, evil communications corrupt good manners.

01:06:55.250 --> 01:06:57.690
Awake to righteousness and sin not.

01:06:58.110 --> 01:07:02.350
For some have not the knowledge of God, I speak this to your shame.

01:07:02.790 --> 01:07:08.310
But some man will say, How are the dead raised up, and with what body do they come?

01:07:08.990 --> 01:07:13.510
Thou fool, that which thou sowest is not quickened, except it die.

01:07:13.950 --> 01:07:20.370
And that which thou sowest, thou sowest not that body that shall be, but bare grain, it

01:07:20.370 --> 01:07:22.890
may chance of wheat or of some other grain.

01:07:23.350 --> 01:07:28.910
But God giveth it a body, as it hath pleased him, and to every seed his own body.

01:07:29.710 --> 01:07:36.350
All flesh is not the same flesh, but there is one kind of flesh of men, another flesh of beasts,

01:07:36.790 --> 01:07:39.570
another of fishes, and another of birds.

01:07:40.210 --> 01:07:43.690
There are also celestial bodies, and bodies terrestrial.

01:07:44.370 --> 01:07:49.150
But the glory of the celestial is one, and the glory of the terrestrial is another.

01:07:49.830 --> 01:07:55.890
There is one glory of the sun, and another glory of the moon, and another glory of the stars,

01:07:55.890 --> 01:07:59.610
for one star differeth from another star in glory.

01:08:00.530 --> 01:08:02.990
So also is the resurrection of the dead.

01:08:03.330 --> 01:08:07.010
It is sown in corruption, it is raised in incorruption.

01:08:07.510 --> 01:08:10.690
It is sown in dishonor, it is raised in glory.

01:08:11.130 --> 01:08:14.230
It is sown in weakness, it is raised in power.

01:08:14.830 --> 01:08:18.750
It is sown a natural body, it is raised a spiritual body.

01:08:19.190 --> 01:08:22.370
There is a natural body, and there is a spiritual body.

01:08:22.370 --> 01:08:27.130
And so it is written, the first man Adam was made a living soul,

01:08:27.450 --> 01:08:30.010
the last Adam was made a quickening spirit.

01:08:30.710 --> 01:08:35.110
Howbeit that was not first which is spiritual, but that which is natural,

01:08:35.410 --> 01:08:37.750
and afterward that which is spiritual.

01:08:38.350 --> 01:08:43.750
The first man is of the earth, earthy, the second man is the Lord from heaven.

01:08:44.410 --> 01:08:49.890
As is the earthy, such are they also that are earthy, and as is the heavenly,

01:08:50.290 --> 01:08:52.350
such are they also that are heavenly.

01:08:52.930 --> 01:08:58.230
And as we have borne the image of the earthy, we shall also bear the image of the heavenly.

01:08:59.050 --> 01:09:03.810
Now this I say, brethren, that flesh and blood cannot inherit the kingdom of God,

01:09:04.250 --> 01:09:07.150
neither doth corruption inherit incorruption.

01:09:07.950 --> 01:09:09.970
Behold, I show you a mystery.

01:09:10.310 --> 01:09:13.830
We shall not all sleep, but we shall all be changed,

01:09:14.090 --> 01:09:17.950
in a moment, in the twinkling of an eye, at the last trump.

01:09:17.950 --> 01:09:22.370
For the trumpet shall sound, and the dead shall be raised incorruptible,

01:09:22.710 --> 01:09:24.170
and we shall be changed.

01:09:24.730 --> 01:09:30.990
For this corruptible must put on incorruption, and this mortal must put on immortality.

01:09:31.690 --> 01:09:35.030
So when this corruptible shall have put on incorruption,

01:09:35.430 --> 01:09:38.030
and this mortal shall have put on immortality,

01:09:38.470 --> 01:09:41.550
then shall be brought to pass the saying that is written,

01:09:41.890 --> 01:09:43.950
Death is swallowed up in victory.

01:09:44.590 --> 01:09:46.870
O death, where is thy sting?

01:09:47.370 --> 01:09:49.450
O grave, where is thy victory?

01:09:50.090 --> 01:09:54.690
The sting of death is sin, and the strength of sin is the law.

01:09:55.150 --> 01:10:00.110
But thanks be to God, which giveth us the victory through our Lord Jesus Christ.

01:10:00.790 --> 01:10:05.070
Therefore, my beloved brethren, be ye steadfast, unmovable,

01:10:05.570 --> 01:10:07.770
always abounding in the work of the Lord,

01:10:08.070 --> 01:10:12.290
forasmuch as ye know that your labor is not in vain in the Lord.

01:10:13.930 --> 01:10:17.730
16. Now concerning the collection for the saints,

01:10:18.110 --> 01:10:22.750
as I have given order to the churches of Galatia, even so do ye.

01:10:23.310 --> 01:10:27.810
Upon the first day of the week, let every one of you lay by him in store,

01:10:28.110 --> 01:10:32.310
as God hath prospered him, that there be no gatherings when I come.

01:10:32.810 --> 01:10:36.710
And when I come, whomsoever ye shall approve by your letters,

01:10:37.090 --> 01:10:40.490
them will I send to bring your liberality unto Jerusalem.

01:10:41.130 --> 01:10:45.330
And if it be meet that I go also, they shall go with me.

01:10:45.990 --> 01:10:49.930
Now I shall come unto you when I shall pass through Macedonia,

01:10:50.250 --> 01:10:52.550
for I do pass through Macedonia.

01:10:53.010 --> 01:10:56.910
And it may be that I will abide, yea, in winter with you,

01:10:57.230 --> 01:11:00.770
that ye may bring me on my journey whithersoever I go.

01:11:01.410 --> 01:11:03.790
For I will not see you now by the way,

01:11:04.010 --> 01:11:07.610
but I trust to tarry a while with you, if the Lord permit.

01:11:07.610 --> 01:11:11.230
But I will tarry at Ephesus until Pentecost,

01:11:11.650 --> 01:11:17.210
for a great door and effectual is opened unto me, and there are many adversaries.

01:11:17.950 --> 01:11:22.470
Now if Timotheus come, see that he may be with you without fear,

01:11:22.910 --> 01:11:26.510
for he worketh the work of the Lord, as I also do.

01:11:27.150 --> 01:11:31.790
Let no man therefore despise him, but conduct him forth in peace,

01:11:32.170 --> 01:11:36.130
that he may come unto me, for I look for him with the brethren.

01:11:36.770 --> 01:11:42.390
As touching our brother Apollos, I greatly desired him to come unto you with the brethren,

01:11:42.850 --> 01:11:45.930
but his will was not at all to come at this time.

01:11:46.410 --> 01:11:49.430
But he will come when he shall have convenient time.

01:11:50.270 --> 01:11:55.190
Watch ye, stand fast in the faith, quit you like men, be strong.

01:11:55.810 --> 01:11:58.330
Let all your things be done with charity.

01:11:58.950 --> 01:12:02.410
I beseech you, brethren, ye know the house of Stephanas,

01:12:02.410 --> 01:12:06.870
that it is the firstfruits of Achaia, and that they have addicted themselves to the

01:12:06.870 --> 01:12:10.790
ministry of the saints, that ye submit yourselves unto such,

01:12:11.050 --> 01:12:14.130
and to every one that helpeth with us and laboreth.

01:12:14.690 --> 01:12:18.970
I am glad of the coming of Stephanas and Fortunatus and Achaicus,

01:12:19.530 --> 01:12:22.910
for that which was lacking on your part they have supplied,

01:12:23.510 --> 01:12:29.650
for they have refreshed my spirit and yours, therefore acknowledge ye them that are such.

01:12:30.410 --> 01:12:36.090
The churches of Asia salute you, Aquila and Percilla salute you much in the Lord,

01:12:36.430 --> 01:12:38.370
with the church that is in their house.

01:12:38.950 --> 01:12:43.950
All the brethren greet you, greet ye one another with an holy kiss.

01:12:44.450 --> 01:12:47.790
The salutation of me, Paul, with mine own hand.

01:12:48.510 --> 01:12:54.150
If any man love not the Lord Jesus Christ, let him be Anathema Marinatha.

01:12:54.790 --> 01:12:57.810
The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you.

01:12:57.810 --> 01:13:02.390
My love be with you all in Christ Jesus. Amen.
